  <description><![CDATA[<p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Hotel Evaldo is a family-run hotel, you'll love the warm welcome from the Lezuo family and their team. It has a traditional alpine feel that carries through to the bedrooms. It's a popular base with Inghams guests wanting to hit the </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Sellaronda</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">. Set back from the centre of Arabba, you can enjoy the peaceful views of the surrounding Dolomiti mountains while still having convenient access to the slopes. </span></p>
<h2>Village location</h2>
<p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">The hotel's about a five-minute walk from the centre of </span><a rel="noopener" data-udi="umb://document/3a67ce6017fa4e79a469b4fc75f18150" href="/{localLink:umb://document/3a67ce6017fa4e79a469b4fc75f18150}" target="_blank" class="editor-rtfLink"><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Arabba,</span></a><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> a charming village with fantastic access to the ski area and the highest point in the Dolomites- the Marmolada. The lifts are a little further away from the centre, with the Portavescovo lift being the nearest, the hotel runs a daily shuttle service in the mornings and afternoons so getting on and off the slopes couldn't be easier. Arabba benefits from having excellent connections to the 'must do' areas of the Dolomites including the Marmolada glacier, the Sellaronda and the Hidden Valley, be sure to ask the team for their recommendations for a lunch stop. </span></p>
<h2>Relaxation</h2>
<p>When you return from a day of skiing the <a data-udi="umb://document/47c7f0773b104efb87f3357e7314f393" href="/{localLink:umb://document/47c7f0773b104efb87f3357e7314f393}" title="The Dolomites Ski Area">Dolomites</a>, head to the lovely wellness area for a relaxing spa session. Have a dip in the pool before relaxing in the jacuzzi, you can then choose between the infrared cabin, Finnish sauna or the steam bath before unwinding in the relaxation area. If you want to train for your next ski adventure, there is a small fitness room with a range of equipment.</p>
<h2>Restaurant</h2>
<p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Start your day at the breakfast buffet which includes a classic continental offering and hot options. When you return tu</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">ck into some afternoon cakes before your tasty four-course dinner. Meals often include typical hearty and filling Ladino dishes, which pair perfectly with a bottle of wine from the wine cellar. </span></p>
<h3>Exclusive to Inghams</h3>
<p>As a ski specialist tour operator we carefully select the very best accommodation in our resorts and package them with flights and transfers, so that you can make the most of your holiday. We have an exclusive agreement with Hotel Evaldo the only UK tour operator to package and sell holidays here - all the more reason to book with Inghams today!</p>
<h3>Why is this an Inghams' Choice property?</h3>
<p><strong>Family-run</strong> - The Hotel Evaldo offers a warm welcome and personal service with a classic alpine feel.</p>
<p><strong>Central location</strong> - You have easy access to the centre of Arabba just a five minute walk away and a daily shuttle to the lifts in the mornings and afternoons.</p>
<p><strong>Wellness area</strong> - After a day exploring the mountain, there is nowhere better to be than relaxing in the wellness facilities which includes a swimming pool, jacuzzi, sauna and steam bath.</p>]]></description>
